The permittee shall file an operations and progress report with the Department by March 31 of each year, on a form prescribed and furnished by the Department, which shall cover the preceding calendar year and shall:
Identify the mine, the permittee, and the permit number;
Identify the location of the operation as to county, district, nearest municipality, and nearest public road;
Report the type of mineral produced, the volume produced, and the value of production of each for the previous year. Individual company data is confidential and may be released only with the permittee's written consent;
State the acreage disturbed by surface mining during the previous year;
State and describe the amount and type of reclamation carried out during the previous year;
Estimate the acreage to be newly disturbed by mining in the next year; and
Provide any additional information or maps which the Department reasonably requires.
